@chooseresidents
    *say
        You have to choose where you would like to live at. Somewhere in the country, city, or suburbs?
    *then
        hear country{
        decrease money by 70,000
        -> country
        }
        hear city{
        decrease money by 200,000
        -> city
        }
        hear suburb{
        decrease money by 150,000
        -> suburb
        }
        
@country
    *say
        You love the wide-open outdoors with no traffic, few neighbors, and planty of room for activiies. The country is where you want to live.
        
    *then
        roll 1d4
            if rollResult == 1{
            ->scenario2
            }
    -> marriage
    

@city
    *say
        You enjoy the hustle and bustle of the City. There are many things to do and go in the city, that is why you wanted to live there
